\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10821394 TT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 Well down there where now is 
the - playing place, the playing field, but - at that time we used to have a - what we used to call the mill pond, and we used to go down there and - in the pond with a raft, old piece of logs and - have our fun down there. Used to be an old foundry there
, years ago, but of course it was all }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3542215\charrsid3634336 derelict}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 
 then and - we used to go in there and - muck about. You had a lot more freedom as children - then than what the children got today. Because of course there wasn't the traffic on the roads, you could play almost anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5537491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 What other games did you play besides making the raft?
