 Well of course - every shop then had errand boys. Which it didn't seem so bad to us because - you always had company wherever you were going on what - road or street you were - delivering there was someone else going that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5537491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 When you left school what was the first job you had to do?
