Oh no. No. I remember one there - to the Liberal Club and - Sir Arthur Karkeek came in, and he was just as - at the time that he was now - he w
as knighted you know, and - he spoke to me, I was playing billiards and he spoke, and I called him - Mr Karkeek, you know, and all the crowd jumped on me - the top nobs up there - for not calling him Sir. Well I - actually forgot it. And I apologised, he 
took it all right but - but it didn't suit the other - top notchers that were there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5537491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 You weren't paying due respect they felt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10821394 TT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 Yes. And - I wasn't courteous enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5537491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 Some families were thought to be rough and others respectable, those that we
re rough was it to do with their way of living would you think or their financial circumstances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10821394 TT  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 
Well no, their - their - they were - better off than we were actually, but it was their - home life I suppose or - how they was brought on, I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5537491 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid3081566\charrsid3634336 Would their roughness include drinking or swearing?
